##Lu Jun, an intensive-care doctor at Tongji Hospital: My colleagues cried when they heard that I had "died"

Emergency Physician Lu Jun, of Tongji Hospital, was one of the most severe in the early days of COVID-19 infection.

On January 5, he developed a fever. A CT scan showed a small infection in his right lower lung. On January 7, when he was reexamined, he developed a double lung infection. Fever lasts for 9 days, after which respiratory difficulty gradually develops.

During Lu Jun's illness, word spread online that he had died. To counter the rumor, on January 23, he commissioned a doctor to take a video of his activities and post it online. "This rumor is too hard on our comrades-in-arms who are fighting on the front line. I took the initiative to dispel it, mainly to cheer them up and hopefully give them the confidence to continue the fight. "

Lu Jun is still being treated at Tongji Hospital, awaiting recovery. "This is a very serious outbreak, but there are not many critically ill patients. As one of the critically ill patients, I was able to pull myself out of danger with the help of medical staff. My own experience tells us not to be afraid, but to be confident, " Lu Jun said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lu Jun was doing rehab.



Suspected to have been infected during a medical visit

Beijing News: When did you become infected with COVID-19?

Lu Jun: I think I got it on duty on January 2, and that night I had more fever patients, about 30. Most of those patients were not diagnosed with new pneumonia, but with flu, some with bacteria, and some with the common cold. NCP was a viral infection, but there was no specific test, very few confirmed patients, not enough knowledge, so not much attention.

Beijing News: WHEN DID FEVER PATIENTS START TO INCREASE?

Lu Jun: It was around January 2nd, when the three doctors came together. I was working the night shift, and I saw over 30 fever patients by myself. At that time, Tongji Hospital fever clinic, but not specifically for new pneumonia (patients) open, emergency department is the main battlefield, I am the Emergency Department of Internal Medicine, so most fever patients, come to the emergency department.

Beijing News: What were the protective measures during that time?

Lu Jun: There were documents at the time saying that there was a new type of pneumonia in Wuhan, but at the time there was too little knowledge of the virus and it was not clear whether it could be transmitted from person to person, so it was just a little bit more protective than before when you were on duty, the normal medical mask for daily work has been upgraded and replaced with the virus-resistant N95 mask. There is no requirement for protective clothing and goggles. It didn't seem weird at the time, since we all wear masks at work.

The diagnosis of new pneumonia in Wuhan was made on January 7

Beijing News: You began to get sick with fever, have you thought about the cause of the disease?

Lu Jun: it was suspected to be the flu virus, so we ran a blood test and a CT scan. Considering the possibility of a viral infection, I did a CT scan, and I remember that the CT scan on January 5 showed a slight infection in the right lower lung, and it got a little worse on January 7 when I reexamined it, and it turned into a double lung infection, and the fever never subsided, it lasted nine days and then developed respiratory distress, which made it feel wrong. I didn't go back to work for nine days with a persistent fever.

Beijing News: A Medical Relief Fund to fund the list, mentioned that the doctor Mr. Lu confirmed on January 7, this person is you?

Lu Jun: It's me. My colleague at Tongji Hospital applied for this Fund for me. Back then, the new coronavirus was called new pneumonia. I'm not sure I'm the first doctor to be diagnosed, but I think I'm the first doctor to be seriously diagnosed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lu Jun's room after he was transferred to Tongji Hospital

Beijing News: What symptoms during the illness?

Lu Jun: started on January 5, had a fever of 38.7 degrees Celsius, then peaked at 39.5 degrees Celsius, fatigue, muscle soreness, difficulty in breathing, then every day infusion, infusion until 4-5 a.m. at the latest, up to a dozen bottles. During the period of illness very anxious, after all, there are young and old, the son is only 3 years old. My wife was the only one who knew that I was sick, and my father was almost 80, and my mother was almost 70, and she didn't tell them. All I could think about was getting better.

Beijing News: How about the current recovery? Is it GonNa Affect Your career?

Lu Jun: He's recovering slowly from a severe illness. It's mostly lung damage, which is consistent with respiratory failure. He talks a lot now, and he can be a little hard to breathe. But now I feel much better than before, as long as the lung function is good, I can go home, and experts say that the physical recovery, should not affect my future work in the emergency room.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Lu Jun's current medication

After he was found dead, he denied it

Beijing News: Can you elaborate on your diagnosis and treatment process?

Lu Jun: When I was treated at this hospital, it was mainly on antiviral drug, steroids, C ball, antibiotics, and inhalation support. On January 17, I was transferred from Tongji Hospital to Jinyintan Hospital, and on January 29, I was transferred back to Tongji Hospital. During treatment at antiviral drug, there were experts from the National Health Commission, as well as experts from Tongji Hospital, who mainly treated patients with infusion, nebulizer and inhalation support.

Beijing News: Did you know that you died of illness?

Lu Jun: I know. I was the one who came up with it. At the time, I was barely out of bed, which is to say I was just getting better. I asked my colleagues who were supporting me at the hospital to help me film my activities to get out of bed and post it on the Internet, because the rumor was so devastating to those who were fighting on the front lines.

One of my colleagues said he cried when he saw the news of my death. I Know My colleagues are very busy and tired, patients are not in a good mood, protective equipment is also in short supply, if I did not have infection, I would certainly be with colleagues in the first line of consultation, but now because of illness did not go, a little regret. I take the initiative to dispel rumors, mainly for the fight in the front-line medical colleagues to cheer, hope to give them the confidence to continue the fight.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After Lu Jun died of illness, doctors at the Union Medical College Hospital helped him dispel rumors on Weibo, China's version of twitter. Screenshot from twitter

Beijing News: Now in Tongji Hospital, his colleagues to see a doctor for you, feel what is different?

Lu Jun: I've been treating myself like a patient, and I've changed my role, and I'm okay with that.

Beijing news: now how to eat to solve it?

Lu Jun: Now my wife brings the food, and she usually puts it in the nurse's station.

Beijing News: After this incident, what do you want to convey to everyone?

Lu Jun: This is a very serious epidemic, but there are not many critical patients. As one of the critical patients, I was able to pull myself out of danger with the help of medical staff. My own experience tells us not to be afraid, to be confident, with the support of the country and the people, the medical staff on the front line are sure to overcome the epidemic.

HSINKING newspaper reporter, Wang Ruiwen, intern, Wang Yahui, editor, Zhao Kaidi on duty editor, Pan Jiakun school to Yang Xuli
